The primary environmental factor that limits the potential rate of electron transport is the availability of light, and this is modulated by leaf absorptance to PAR (Fig.Â 6, Case 1). Under limiting light intensities, the potential rate of electron flow through Cyt b6f\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
