				\begin{document}$$\hbox {b}_{6}\hbox {f}$$\end{document} and PS I is a rectangular hyperbolic function of light intensity (Fig.Â 6a). The geometry of this function demonstrates that light drives a trade-off between the speed and efficiency of electron transport: the increase in speed is caused by the increased supply of reduced plastoquinone to Cyt b6f\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
