				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\hbox {CO}_2$$\end{document} assimilation as well as the absorbed quantum yield for CO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\hbox {CO}_2$$\end{document} assimilation (Fig.Â 6c, d). Increasing the absorptance to PAR drives simultaneous increases in the rates of photosynthesis and decreases in the absorbed quantum yields. The basis of these effects is that increasing the absorptance to PAR increases the rate at which open reaction centers are driven to the closed state, and therefore increases the accumulation of closed reaction centers.

