We begin with the effects of the level of connectivity and mobility of the pigment system (Fig.Â 8, Cases 9 and 10). The exact mechanistic basis of PS II antennae connectivity, and its magnitude in quantitative terms, are important unknowns because connectivity has the potential to influence both photochemical and non-photochemical quenching. In this initial simulation, we have kept the absorption cross-sections fixed and varied connectivity alone (Fig.Â 8, Case 9). With this approach, connectivity has no effect on electron transport or CO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
